<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
An <a title="In-Line" href="In-Line">in-line</a> folding device on a <a title="Web Press" href="Web_Press">web press</a>. The jaw folder essentially consists of a set of cylinders. As a paper web is carried around one cylinder, it is cut into indiovidual sheets or signatures, each of which is forced by a <a title="Tucker Blade" href="Tucker_Blade">tucker blade</a> (which creates a slight protrusion on paper) into a set of jaws on an adjacent cylinder. As the web is forced through these jaws, a fold is created. The jaw folder is essentially used to cut and fold a web into individual cylinders. 
</p>
